  <text>
    <body>
      <div>
        <listEvent>
          <event type="governance">
            <p>1. <date when="-0132">In the year <date calendar="#cal_Macedonian">180</date></date>, kings began to rule in 
              <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName>.</p>
          </event>
        </listEvent>
      </div>
      <div>
        <listEvent>
          <event type="accession">
            <p>2. <date when="-0046"><!-- Author must mean 44 BC. Not sure how to handle this. -->In the year <date calendar="#cal_Macedonian">266</date></date>
              <persName><name type="person" ref="#Augustus"><roleName type="nobility">Augustus</roleName> <surname>Caesar</surname></name></persName>was made emperor.</p>
          </event>
        </listEvent>
      </div>
      <div>
        <listEvent>
          <event type="birth">
            <p>3. <date when="-0003">In the year <date calendar="#cal_Macedonian">309</date></date>
              <persName><name type="person" ref="#Christ"><addName>our Lord</addName></name></persName> was born.</p>
          </event>
        </listEvent>
      </div>
      <div>
        <listEvent>
          <event type="building">
            <p>4. <date when="0088">In the year <date calendar="#cal_Macedonian">400</date></date>,
              <persName><name type="person" ref="#Abgar1"><forename>Abgar</forename> the <roleName>king</roleName></name></persName> built a mausoleum for himself.</p>
          </event>
        </listEvent>
      </div>
      <div>
        <listEvent>
          <event type="apostasy">
            <p>5. <date when="0137">In the year <date calendar="#cal_Macedonian">449</date></date> <persName><name type="person" ref="#Marcion">Marcion</name></persName> forsook the 
              <orgName>Catholic Church</orgName>.</p>
          </event>
        </listEvent>
      </div>
      <div>
        <listEvent>
          <event type="birth">
            <p>6. <date when="0154-07-11"><date calendar="#cal_Macedonian">The year 465, in the month Tammuz, on the eleventh day</date> (i.e., July 11th, 154 A.D.)</date>,
              <persName><name type="person" ref="#Bardaisan">Bardesanes</name></persName> was born.</p>
          </event>
        </listEvent>
      </div>
      <div>
        <listEvent>
          <event type="conquest">
            <p>7. <persName><name type="person" ref="#Lucius"><forename>Lucius</forename> 
              <roleName type="nobility"><!-- problem, earlier Caesar was a family name, by now it's become a title -->Caesar</roleName></name></persName>,
              with his <persName><!-- But, of course, this is not a name. I'm not sure why <listPerson> and <person> elements won't validate. --><name ref="#Commodus">brother</name></persName>, subjugated <orgName type="state"><!-- org or place? -->the Parthians</orgName> to 
             <orgName type="state">the <region>Romans</region></orgName> <date when="0166">in the fifth year of his reign</date>.</p>
            <listRelation>
              <relation name="sibling" mutual="#Lucius #Commodus"></relation><!-- BUT, does this actually get us what we need? I don't actually know.-->
            </listRelation>
          </event>
        </listEvent>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
